Vendored fork of pub.dev kindle_unpack 0.1.1 (packages/kindle_unpack).

Upstream pins archive ^3.6.1. The app is on archive 4.x. Every archive API the
package uses (Archive, ArchiveFile(name, size, data), addFile,
ZipEncoder.encode) is backwards compatible in 4.x except the two spots below.

Changes in lib/src/epub.dart:

1. mimetype entry stored uncompressed. archive 3.x used an `ArchiveFile.compress`
   bool; archive 4.x uses the `CompressionType` enum `compression`:

  final mimetype = ArchiveFile(
    'mimetype',
    _epubMimetype.length,
    Uint8List.fromList(_epubMimetype.codeUnits),
- )..compress = false;
+ )..compression = CompressionType.none;

2. ZipEncoder.encode returns a non-null List<int> in archive 4.x, so the old
   null guard is dead code (analyzer flags unnecessary_null_comparison):

  final encoded = ZipEncoder().encode(archive);
- if (encoded == null) {
-   throw StateError('zip encoding produced null output');
- }
  return Uint8List.fromList(encoded);

pubspec.yaml dependency also relaxed from `archive: ^3.6.1` to `archive: ^4.0.9`.

Only lib/ is consumed, so the upstream test/ suite, the dev_dependencies
(epubx, lints, test), and analysis_options.yaml were dropped from the vendored
copy.

When re-vendoring a newer upstream release, re-apply these changes if the
mimetype-store line and null guard are still present.
